, \"to\": 2941}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic and Paralympic Games history\", \"from\": 2945, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"a smartphone\", \"from\": 2987, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 3019, \"to\": 3029}, {\"ngram\": \"The usual rules\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3045}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 3057, \"to\": 3065}, {\"ngram\": \"personal belongings\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3099}, {\"ngram\": \"phones\", \"from\": 3109, \"to\": 3115}, {\"ngram\": \"the ceremony\", \"from\": 3120, \"to\": 3132}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As such, traditionally, the podium was always photographed by accredited media from afar.However, this year, for the first time in history, the IOC will allow athletes to bring their phones, i.e., the Galaxy Z Flip 6 Olympic Edition, to the Paris 2024 podium, where they will take selfies and upload them in real-time to the official Athlete365 app.There is no sign that Samsung will ever sell this exclusive phone to the general public.\", \"from\": 3134, \"to\": 3571, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3278, \"end\": 3281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3047884197374671e-16, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 3335, \"end\": 3348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Galaxy Z Flip\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samsung_Galaxy_Z_Flip\"}, {\"begin\": 3375, \"end\": 3385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999989295247, \"rank\": 1.0704818935517578e-09, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \